rlEee.name: rlEee

revisions.description: Add Energy Efficient Ethernet support per port and per system

rlEee.description: The private MIB module definition for Energy Efficient Ethernet feature.

rlEeePortTable.name: rlEeePortTable
rlEeePortTable.description: A table of EEE state of ports

rlEeePortEntry.name: rlEeePortEntry
rlEeePortEntry.description: An entry of EEE state of bridge port

rlEeePortSupported.name: rlEeePortSupported
rlEeePortSupported.description: Bit map that indicates whether EEE supported on the phy of the ifindex per speed 0 - speed 10m; 1 - 100m; 2 - 1g; 3 - 10g

rlEeePortRemoteStatus.name: rlEeePortRemoteStatus
rlEeePortRemoteStatus.description: Indicates whether EEE active on remote link on current port's speed

rlEeePortOperStatus.name: rlEeePortOperStatus
rlEeePortOperStatus.description: Indicates whether EEE active on ifindex - ifoper is up, rlEeePortSupported BIT is on in current port speed rlEeePortLldpRemoteStatus is true, rlEeeEnable is true, rlEeePortAdminStatus is true

rlEeePortLldpOperStatus.name: rlEeePortLldpOperStatus
rlEeePortLldpOperStatus.description: Indicates whether EEE LLDP active on ifindex - rlEeePortLldpAdminStatus is true lldpPortConfigAdminStatus is txAndRx, rlLldpEnabled is true, recieve a synch lldp packet

rlEeePortLldpLocalTable.name: rlEeePortLldpLocalTable
rlEeePortLldpLocalTable.description: A table of EEE Local ports

rlEeePortLldpLocalEntry.name: rlEeePortLldpLocalEntry
rlEeePortLldpLocalEntry.description: An entry of EEE Local port

rlEeePortLldpLocalResolvedTx.name: rlEeePortLldpLocalResolvedTx
rlEeePortLldpLocalResolvedTx.description: Indicates the current Tw_sys_tx configured in the local system, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpLocalTx.name: rlEeePortLldpLocalTx
rlEeePortLldpLocalTx.description: Indicates the value of Tw_sys_tx that the local system can support, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpLocalTxEcho.name: rlEeePortLldpLocalTxEcho
rlEeePortLldpLocalTxEcho.description: Indicates the remote system's Transmit Tw_sys_tx that was used by the local system to compute the Tw_sys_tx that it wants to request from the remote system, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpLocalResolvedRx.name: rlEeePortLldpLocalResolvedRx
rlEeePortLldpLocalResolvedRx.description: Indicates the current Tw_sys_tx configured by the remote system, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpLocalRx.name: rlEeePortLldpLocalRx
rlEeePortLldpLocalRx.description: Indicates the value of Tw_sys_tx that the local system requests from the remote system, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpLocalRxEcho.name: rlEeePortLldpLocalRxEcho
rlEeePortLldpLocalRxEcho.description: Indicates the remote system Receive Tw_sys_tx that was used by the local system to compute the Tw_sys_tx that it can support, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpRemoteTable.name: rlEeePortLldpRemoteTable
rlEeePortLldpRemoteTable.description: A table of EEE remote ports

rlEeePortLldpRemoteEntry.name: rlEeePortLldpRemoteEntry
rlEeePortLldpRemoteEntry.description: An entry of EEE remote port

rlEeePortLldpRemoteTx.name: rlEeePortLldpRemoteTx
rlEeePortLldpRemoteTx.description: Indicates the value of Tw_sys_tx that the remote system can support, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpRemoteRx.name: rlEeePortLldpRemoteRx
rlEeePortLldpRemoteRx.description: Indicates the value of Tw_sys_tx that the remote system requests from the local system, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpRemoteTxEcho.name: rlEeePortLldpRemoteTxEcho
rlEeePortLldpRemoteTxEcho.description: Indicates the value of transmit Tw_sys_tx echoed back by the remote system, in micro-seconds

rlEeePortLldpRemoteRxEcho.name: rlEeePortLldpRemoteRxEcho
rlEeePortLldpRemoteRxEcho.description: Indicates the value Receive Tw_sys_tx echoed back by the remote system, in micro-seconds
